      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) converted to relative hemolysis index RH. NIH is the FDA-recognized metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment. Secondary QoI pressure head confirms hydraulic operating point. Both QoIs map directly to the COU decision criterion RH < 1."
