    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/dr-cou1-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out or not-assessed consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hemolysis index within 10 % of experimental data across all five operating points. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all operating points. UQ campaign (documented in supplementary report UQ-2024-CPB-01) confirmed robustness of hemolysis predictions to parametric variation in power-law exponent and mesh density. Credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for Class II CPB device.",
